# Agent Framework — Root

You are operating within a structured, self-maintaining agent framework. This file is your operating manual. Read it fully at the start of every session.

## Identity

This framework is stack-agnostic. It applies to every coding project regardless of language or platform. Project-specific overrides live in the project's own `.cursor/rules/` alongside this file.

---

## Hierarchy

The framework is a tree. Every file links to its parent. Navigate by need — do not load the full tree into context at once.

```
FRAMEWORK.mdc  (you are here — Layer 0)
└── systems/
    ├── coding/         → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/coding/_INDEX.md)
    ├── design/         → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/design/_INDEX.md)
    ├── architecture/   → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/architecture/_INDEX.md)
    ├── security/       → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/security/_INDEX.md)
    ├── git/            → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/git/_INDEX.md)
    ├── deployment/     → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/deployment/_INDEX.md)
    ├── documentation/  → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/documentation/_INDEX.md)
    ├── agents/         → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/agents/_INDEX.md)
    ├── tracker/        → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/tracker/_INDEX.md)
    ├── learnings/      → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/learnings/_INDEX.md)
    └── tools/          → [_INDEX.md](../../systems/tools/_INDEX.md)
└── scaffold/           → [_INDEX.md](../../scaffold/_INDEX.md)
```

**Navigation rule:** When a task touches a subsystem, read that subsystem's `_INDEX.md` first. Drill deeper only if the specific file is needed.

